McCurdy  . Compare   Murdoch   and   Moriarty  . The name was also used to Anglicize <i>Mac Murchaidh</i> (see   McMorrow  )."]}]},{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":0,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":13,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":22,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda Mortimer was born in 1315, in Hodnet, Shropshire, England as the daughter of Mortimer. She had at least 2 sons with Ralphe II Lingen. She died in 1346, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1315–1346":"1315–1346","1313–Male":"1313–Surnud","1334–1399":"1334–1399","1340–1406":"1340–1406","–Male":"Surnud","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1399":"1399","1453":"1453","1340":"1340","Abt 1340  (yr son)":"umbes 1340","1406":"1406","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Hodnet, Shropshire, England":"Hodnet, Shropshire, England","Sutton, Herefordshire, England":"Sutton, Herefordshire, England","Lingen, Herefordshire, England":"Lingen, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"1315–1346":"1315–1346","1313–Male":"1313–Kuollut","1334–1399":"1334–1399","1340–1406":"1340–1406","–Male":"Kuollut","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1313":"1313","1334":"1334","1399":"1399","1453":"1453","1340":"1340","Abt 1340  (yr son)":"noin 1340","1406":"1406","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Hodnet, Shropshire, England":"Hodnet, Shropshire, England","Sutton, Herefordshire, England":"Sutton, Herefordshire, England","Lingen, Herefordshire, England":"Lingen, Herefordshire, England"},"fr":{"1315–1346":"1315–1346","1313–Male":"1313–Décédé","1334–1399":"1334–1399","1340–1406":"1340–1406","–Male":"Décédé","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1313":"1313"